This paper is about image smoothing using deep neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach for model generation, which involves network interpolation and extrapolation, and uses a double-state aggregation module. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which could also make it relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents experimental results that involve visual analysis of images, which could also make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
